

=Bio=

"Yihong Ding is a PhD candidate of computer science at Brigham Young University. He is also affiliated with DERI Innsbruck. His research includes Semantic Web, annotation, data extraction, and ontology generation, matching, and reuse. Besides his formal research, Yihong is an active thinker and writer who has a distinctive view on the future of the World Wide Web and Web evolution. These viewpoints are primarily blogged in Thinking Space (his personal blog) and SemanticFocus (as a contributing author). Yihong was born in Zhejiang, China, and he has an M.Eng. degree in Mechanical Engineering."
